INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2300','letter','1801-01-13','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Joseph','Alston','','I have already written to you by the post to tell you that I shall be happy to see you whenever you choose','ltr_tba2300.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2301','letter','1801-01-24','Poughkeepsie','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Joseph','Alston','','Thus far have we advanced on this &quot;terrible&quot; journey, from which you predicted so many evils, Without meeting even with inconvenience. How strange that Mr. Alston should be wrong.','ltr_tba2301.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2302','letter','1802-06-26','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Joseph','Alston','','When, when will the month of October come? It appears to recede instead of approaching; and time, which extinguishes all other sorrows, serves but to increase mine','ltr_tba2302.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2303','letter','1802-06-28','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Joseph','Alston','','And do you, indeed, miss your Theo.? Do you really find happiness indissolubly blended with her presence?','ltr_tba2303.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2304','letter','1802-09-03','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Joseph','Alston','','What a pity minds could not be made sensible of each other\'s approach! Why were we not so formed, that when your thoughts, your soul were with your Theo., hers could be enabled, by the finest sensation of sympathy, to meet it.','ltr_tba2304.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2305','letter','1802-09-30','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Joseph','Alston','','You have been imprudent, and all my fears are fulfilled. Without any one near you to feel for you, to attend to you, to watch every change and share every pain. Your wife only could do that.','ltr_tba2305.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2306','letter','1802-10-30','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Joseph','Alston','','You already know the result of my confinement in bed. It certainly relieved me for some time, which proves how easily that cure would have succeeded at first.','ltr_tba2306.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2307','letter','1802-03-17','Clifton','SC','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','Ever since the date of my last letter, for it was not forwarded till some days after, I have been quite ill; till within these two or three days totally unable to write.','ltr_tba2307.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2308','letter','1803-06-04','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','Encore stupid. For Heaven\'s sake, what do you imagine I can find to say once a day that is worth saying','ltr_tba2308.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2309','letter','1803-06-09','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','I received yesterday your three letters of the 5th and 6th. They made me laugh, yet I pity you, and have really a fellow feeling for you.','ltr_tba2309.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2310','letter','1803-06-10','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','We have been dining with Mrs. Laight to-day, and have been much amused.','ltr_tba2310.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2311','letter','1803-06-11','Philadelphia','PA','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','Continuation of the Story of the Loves of Reubon and Celeste','ltr_tba2311.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2312','letter','1803-06-14','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','As to Celeste, \'voila mon\' opinion. She meant, from the beginning, to say that awful word-- \'yes\'; but not choosing to say it immediately, she told you that \'you\' had furnished her with arguments against matrimony','ltr_tba2312.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2313','letter','1803-07-20','Ballston','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','On arriving here we found that your letter to H. Walton had not been received; but we have been very fortunate in getting a house entirely to ourselves','ltr_tba2313.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2314','letter','1803-10-16','Washington','MD','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','We arrived here yesterday somewhat fatigued. I was, however, very happy to find myself at Washington','ltr_tba2314.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2315','letter','1803-10-21','Petersburgh','NC','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','I confess I feel myself growing quite cross on the journey, and it is really to be feared that, unless we soon finish it, the serene tranquillity of my placid temper may be injured.','ltr_tba2315.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2316','letter','1803-10-29','Clifton','SC','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','Thank Heaven, my dear father, I am at Lumberton, and within a few days of rest.','ltr_tba2316.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2317','letter','1803-11-08','Clifton','SC','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','But you, who always put the best construction on my words and deeds, will allow, that a place in which we have suffered much and run a risk of suffering more must be unpleasant.','ltr_tba2317.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2318','letter','1803-11-19','Charleston','SC','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','those pretty little playthings from D. M\'Kinnon delighted me. I looked at them over and over, with as much pleasure as a miser over his hoard.','ltr_tba2318.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2319','letter','1803-12-01','Clifton','SC','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','My health is infinitely improved, and I attribute it to nothing but the continual bustle I have been kept in for three weeks past.','ltr_tba2319.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2320','letter','1803-12-10','Clifton','SC','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Aaron','Burr','','Behold me again at Clifton; and, in good truth, I begin to be cloyed with the delights of bustle.','ltr_tba2320.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2321','letter','1805-08-06','The Oaks','SC','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Joseph','Alston','','I cannot tell; but something whispers me that my end approaches.','ltr_tba2321.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_tba2322','letter','1802-06-24','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Alston','','Joseph','Alston','','We arrived yesterday morning, exactly the eighth day since I left you. Our passage was pleasant, inasmuch as we had no storms, and the most obliging, attentive captain.','ltr_tba2322.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
